<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/517: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cramp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-28T17:00:00-04:00">August 28, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>16. The following telegram from the American Chargé d’affaires in
                                Managua is repeated for your confidential information.</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of telegram No. 86 of August 28, 7 a.m., from the
                                Chargé in Nicaragua, printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                            <p>Without making any inquiries whatever please telegraph your opinion
                                in this matter.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>